<span class="header1">VISUAL PRODUCTION</span>
<p>Jobs in this field are concerned with producing visual 
materials.  These materials can play an important role in helping 
people to understand information. They make written materials more 
interesting as well.  Here are three examples.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Broadcast Journalist</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BE/43067.jpg" 
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Audiovisual Production 
Director" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you are interested in radio and movies and 
you think you would like to join the military, consider becoming a 
broadcast journalist. A broadcast journalist participates in the 
production of radio or television programs.  For example, if you 
were in the military, you might work for Armed Forces Radio as a 
script writer or announcer.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Usually, you need a college degree for this 
job.  The military also provides training.  Experience is 
important.  Part-time jobs and extracurricular activities could play 
a role in getting a job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>Your salary is based on your experience and 
skill.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Graphic Designer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BE/43312.jpg" 
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Graphic Designer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A graphic designer helps to create visual 
displays that appear in many kinds of publications.  As a graphic 
designer, you would make signs, charts, tables, and other visual 
displays.  Your work could appear in magazines, training manuals, 
newspapers, and other publications.  You need to be creative to do 
well in this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A college degree is not required. Because 
graphic design is highly computer-oriented today, computer skills 
would be beneficial to aquiring a job in this field.  You may also 
want to consider attending an art school that offers courses in 
graphic design.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary you receive depends on your 
experience and skill.  It also depends on where you work.  
Experience will help in getting a job.  Part-time jobs and volunteer 
work can be important.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Photojournalist</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BE/43060.jpg" 
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Photojournalist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like to take photographs, you might 
become a photojournalist. In this job, you would photograph 
important events for newspapers, magazines, and television.  A 
photojournalist's job is much like that of a reporter.  The 
difference is that you would use photos to tell the story.  To be 
successful, you need to be brave enough to follow a hunch.  You also 
have to be able to make quick decisions.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A Bachelor's Degree is needed to become a 
photojournalist. Experience is important also.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary is from $17,000 to $45, 
000.</blockquote>

